parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls while driving
the transmission slips or hesitates
the RPM gauge fluctuates wildly
the vehicle loses power
the transmission fails to engage
and the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
the vehicle loses power
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Improperly Heat-Treated Piston Oil Rings
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of motive power, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways. In some cases, the engine failure can also cause oil to leak onto the engine, potentially leading to a fire.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving
the check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle loses power
the engine overheats
the vehicle jerks or shakes violently
the engine consumes excessive oil
the oil plug falls out
and the vehicle catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of motive power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks while shifting gears
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle loses power
the check engine warning light illuminates.
